1
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,000
Can I team up

2
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:54,680
with you?

3
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,760
Sure.

4
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:07,850
Alright, everyone, put the plates you got

5
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:10,039
into the boxes you received.

6
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,440
Pick up the hammer on your workbench.

7
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:16,280
When I count down from three,

8
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:18,520
smash the plate.

9
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,960
Three, two, one.

10
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:22,840
Smash!

11
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,170
You do it.

12
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,410
It's fine. You do it.

13
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:32,000
Alright, you have 30 minutes

14
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:35,039
to restore the smashed porcelain plates.

15
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:38,200
Use the tools currently on your workbench.

16
00:01:39,039 --> 00:01:39,600
Begin.

17
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,520
This is a bit too shattered.

18
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:45,039
Sir, but we don't know how to glue it.

19
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:46,320
Use your talent.

20
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,160
Hurry up.

21
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:51,000
I think I smashed it into too many pieces.

22
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:52,120
I'm fine.

23
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,320
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

24
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:54,560
Impossible.

25
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,200
I shouldn't have hit it so hard just now.

26
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,600
This is really baffling.

27
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,560
Do you need my help?

28
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:34,400
No.

29
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,320
No need.

30
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,720
Then help me throw it away.

31
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,000
Time's up.

32
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,320
Stop what you're doing.

33
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:13,520
Let me take a look

34
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:15,720
and check the results of your hard work.

35
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,040
This one is a fail.

36
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,960
This is a fail.

37
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:23,760
Fail.

38
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,600
Is this okay, sir?

39
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,700
This one is not bad.

40
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,280
Thank you, sir.

41
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,240
Did you try your best?

42
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:31,840
Yes, I did.

43
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,900
I tried my best too.

44
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,780
As long as you tried your best.

45
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,400
This... can pass, right?

46
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,770
I shouldn't have smashed it to pieces.

47
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,560
It's acceptable.

48
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,480
65 points.

49
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:57,840
Only 65?

50
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:58,360
What?

51
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,850
Do you want a perfect score?

52
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,610
If you want a perfect score,

53
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,720
you can take your diploma and graduate now.

54
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:05,560
Why so mean?

55
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,960
Is he overreacting?

56
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,080
Class, now

57
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,880
pick up the hammers on your workbenches again.

58
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,960
Break your plates again.

59
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:14,720
Here.

60
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,400
Oh my god.

61
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,640
We just fixed it.

62
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,399
Okay, excuse me.

63
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,880
I'll take some porcelain pieces.

64
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,600
One piece, two pieces.

65
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,560
Excuse me.

66
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,040
I'll take one piece from each group.

67
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,120
Starting now,

68
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,330
you will take the remaining pieces

69
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,690
and restore them again.

70
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,480
No way.

71
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,880
Sir, you took a piece away.

72
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:34,760
It's incomplete.

73
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:35,480
How are we supposed to fix it?

74
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:35,840
Exactly.

75
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:38,320
Are porcelain pieces excavated from the ground

76
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,320
always intact?

77
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,720
I will check them in the next class.

78
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,600
Class dismissed. Goodbye.

79
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,200
Goodbye, sir.

80
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,520
Xu Xiao.

81
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:53,360
Where are you going now?

82
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:56,040
You don't have to worry about this homework.

83
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,440
I can finish it by myself.

84
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,320
But we are in the same group.

85
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:03,740
I'm used to working alone.

86
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,210
Don't worry.

87
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,740
Mr. Yue won't find out.

88
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,400
I want to help too.

89
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,380
Luckily you teamed up with me.

90
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:20,130
Otherwise I would definitely be left out.

91
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:22,400
So,

92
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,300
I want to do my best to help you too.

93
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,250
Where is this place?

94
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,320
This is the antique shop where I work.

95
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,080
Work?

96
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:39,280
Aren't you going to finish the assignment with me?

97
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:05,960
Why did we

98
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,360
come all the way here to do the restoration?

99
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:10,200
I have my own restoration tools here.

100
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,720
They are more complete than the school's,

101
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,440
making the restoration more convenient.

102
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:14,840
This set of restoration tools

103
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:17,100
looks like it's been used for a long time.

104
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:18,760
It was a gift from someone.

105
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:19,360
Who is it?

106
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,060
Let's get started.

107
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:27,760
Okay.

108
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:43,000
I hope I can be of help.

109
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,159
All right.

110
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,600
Let's start mixing the glue now.

111
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,120
Isn't there ready-made glue?

112
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,200
Different types of porcelain

113
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:55,360
require different types

114
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,560
of adhesives or glue.

115
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:57,400
We need to ensure the adhesive

116
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,330
matches in transparency and color

117
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,440
with the restored porcelain.

118
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,240
So it's best to mix it ourselves.

119
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:04,880
Okay.

120
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:07,200
Three parts of glue A,

121
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,530
and one part of glue B is enough.

122
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,980
Mix them together,

123
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,760
then apply it evenly.

124
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:17,810
Give it a try.

125
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,040
Okay.

126
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,360
Piece them together,

127
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,330
then use your hands to feel the fit.

128
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,560
Don't put your hands near the gap.

129
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,820
You might get pinched.

130
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,560
Do you know how to apply tape?

131
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,159
I can do this.

132
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,080
Apply tape

133
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,930
to make the gap more secure.

134
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,680
What is this?

135
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:44,980
Wax sheets.

136
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:46,760
Normally,

137
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:49,690
it is hard to restore the missing parts directly.

138
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,690
So we need to use melted wax sheets.

139
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:54,320
Then mold the shape from an intact area.

140
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,640
Get the ratio of plaster and water right.

141
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,370
Add water and stir thoroughly.

142
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:01,640
The next step is to use its fluidity to fill the gaps,

143
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,500
shaping out the general outline.

144
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,040
This step feels like DIY.

145
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,040
Making a cake?

146
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,000
It does look a bit like it.

147
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:13,640
Lord Pang.

148
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,280
Stop shouting.

149
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,920
I'm coming.

150
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,160
I'll feed you.

151
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,220
Why is there someone up there?

152
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,080
He probably has been here all along.

153
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:24,800
Stop shouting. I'm coming.

154
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,330
Has he always been up there?

155
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,600
Stop shouting. I beg you.

156
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,680
Who is he?

157
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,920
The boss of this shop.

158
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,520
Xiao Xu.

159
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,640
Why is there an extra person?

160
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,280
Is there a situation?

161
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,240
This is my classmate.

162
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,650
We are doing our assignment together.

163
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:45,420
Coming.

164
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,560
Lord Pang.

165
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,440
Here, it's yours.

166
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,340
Don't mind him.

167
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,860
He's always like this.

168
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,240
Let's continue.

169
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:55,760
Okay.

170
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,920
It's almost done, right?

171
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,860
Not even close.

172
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,160
We still need to use 600 and 2000-grit sandpaper

173
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,290
for fine polishing.

174
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,760
Then apply jade polishing powder to a piece of cowhide

175
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,020
for mirror polishing.

176
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:21,720
How long will that take?

177
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,340
When you're restoring it,

178
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,730
what's on your mind?

179
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,560
I just think about

180
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,560
restoring it as quickly as possible

181
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,960
so I can finish the assignment.

182
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,440
If you only treat it

183
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,440
as an assignment,

184
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,300
you won't do a good job.

185
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:38,480
Oh.

186
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,680
Every restoration

187
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,440
is a conversation

188
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:47,640
between the ceramics and the restorer.

189
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,960
Every gap

190
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,560
and every tiny crack

191
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,640
is its way of confiding in us.

192
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,740
But its voice is very small and delicate.

193
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:58,640
Only by feeling it with your heart

194
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,120
can you hear its voice.

195
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:09,480
Look.

196
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,000
The parts repaired with plaster

197
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,440
have a huge color difference from the original.

198
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,680
If we make it as close to the original color as possible,

199
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:17,140
would it look a bit better?

200
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:20,040
Restoration for exhibition doesn't require coloring.

201
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:20,800
But I

202
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:25,160
still want to make it complete.

203
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,960
Do you have any paint here?

204
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:40,220
You know how to mix colors?

205
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,920
I learned a bit of drawing when I was a kid.

206
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,720
But my mom said

207
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:46,400
that learning to draw is too tiring

208
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,520
and unstable.

209
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:51,280
So I stopped learning it later.

210
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,880
Is it okay?

211
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,260
You are very talented.

212
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,480
Xu Xiao,

213
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:26,280
this plate tonight,

214
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,400
can I take it home?

215
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:29,600
Sure.

216
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,160
Mom.

217
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,000
Cencen,

218
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:55,960
come.

219
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,680
I washed some grapes for you.

220
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,160
Okay.

221
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,040
Mom, look at my plate.

222
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,440
It looks great.

223
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:05,600
You've shown it to me several times since you got back today.

224
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,480
Are you tired?

225
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:08,200
You've been doing this all day.

226
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:08,800
Not at all.

227
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:11,440
Studying is important,

228
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,120
but your health is more important.

229
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,000
Without a healthy body,

230
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,200
nothing has meaning.

231
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,330
So, don't overexert yourself.

232
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:18,320
I know.

233
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,860
Here, eat some grapes.

234
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,610
Here, you have some too.

235
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,200
Yours is too rough.

236
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,000
It fails.

237
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,400
Mr., what about ours?

238
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,600
Yours is also too rough.

239
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:36,320
It fails.

240
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,560
What's that gray stuff on your plate?

241
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,440
Play-Doh.

242
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,400
You use this to repair the broken parts?

243
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:42,960
Smart, right?

244
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,620
Saves a lot of trouble, right?

245
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:47,080
When Mr. Yue pinches it later, it'll lose its shape.

246
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,000
Let's see what you do then.

247
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,640
Exactly.

248
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:49,600
Xu Xiao.

249
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,320
Have you finished repairing your porcelain plate?

250
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:51,980
Yeah, yeah.

251
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,060
When did you repair it?

252
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,560
We never saw you in the repair room.

253
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:57,600
We repaired it off-campus.

254
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,730
You actually met up alone off-campus.

255
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,120
We just went to finish our assignment.

256
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:02,880
Really?

257
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,000
Let me see yours.

258
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,600
Yours is all dented.

259
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,800
This is unqualified.

260
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,760
Unqualified again.

261
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,340
Let me see yours over here.

262
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,040
I wonder how many people Mr. Yue

263
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,160
will let pass this time.

264
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:16,120
I heard

265
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:18,080
no one can get credits from his class.

266
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,320
I really tried my best this time.

267
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:19,800
Yeah.

268
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,440
What is this thing you made?

269
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,240
Unqualified.

270
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,920
Failed again.

271
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:24,920
I told you.

272
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,240
It definitely won't work.

273
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,040
Failed.

274
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,040
Let me see yours.

275
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,600
Yours is not bad.

276
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,960
You even touched up the color yourself.

277
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,120
Not bad. Very good.

278
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:35,560
Thank you.

279
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:36,240
You passed.

280
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,500
So what's the score this time?

281
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,000
What was it last time?

282
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,400
Last time it was 65.

283
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:42,920
70.

284
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,640
All right, class.

285
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:46,400
Come on, put the plates down

286
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,730
upside down on the desk.

287
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,640
Pick up the little hammers on your desks.

288
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:52,640
No way.

289
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,080
Yes, here we go again.

290
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,740
Come on, pick up your hammers.

291
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:56,620
Hammers again.

292
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:57,640
What's wrong?

293
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,200
We worked so hard to restore this.

294
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,000
I can't bear to do it.

295
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:00,730
Cut the crap.

296
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:01,280
Come on.

297
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:01,960
Then I'll do it.

298
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:02,920
Three, two, one, smash.

299
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,320
Bring it on.

300
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:04,450
I don't understand.

301
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:04,960
Come on.

302
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,400
Okay, step aside.

303
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:08,280
Watch out for the shards.

304
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:08,960
Collecting them again.

305
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:09,800
Watch your hands.

306
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:10,760
Careful.

307
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:11,280
Come here.

308
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:13,610
I've collected all the porcelain pieces.

309
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:14,760
Okay.

310
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:15,200
Taking so many.

311
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,730
Why are you taking them all?

312
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,200
All the broken pieces of the plate are here.

313
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,320
Can you still restore your plates

314
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,680
within one class?

315
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:24,160
Absolutely impossible.

316
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,840
Help, no way.

317
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:26,480
How is that possible?

318
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,760
This is too difficult.

319
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:28,160
Yeah.

320
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:30,840
We couldn't even complete

321
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,160
the simpler tasks in the previous two classes.

322
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:32,880
Right.

323
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,140
Not to mention you,

324
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:35,760
even experts

325
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:37,850
would find it hard to do.

326
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,560
After the founding of the PRC,

327
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:40,840
our archaeologists

328
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,610
excavated a large number of

329
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:46,320
Ming Dynasty blue and white dragon vat porcelain fragments.

330
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:49,720
There were so many that several warehouses couldn't hold them.

331
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:50,760
But up to now,

332
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,720
how many do you think have been restored?

333
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,520
A hundred.

334
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,760
Two hundred.

335
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:56,560
Twenty.

336
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:56,960
Ten.

337
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,800
None of those.

338
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,120
Up to now,

339
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:03,240
only three have been restored.

340
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,400
Three.

341
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:04,920
Yes.

342
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:07,820
Relic restoration

343
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:11,160
takes a long time.

344
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:13,720
and a persevering attitude.

345
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,840
In these two classes,

346
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,320
you went through the process

347
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,980
of starting over three times.

348
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,560
You will go through this process

349
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,440
in your future lives

350
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,480
countless times.

351
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:25,400
Students,

352
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:26,800
I hope that

353
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,640
since you are in this class,

354
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:29,700
You must establish

355
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:33,160
the determination to dedicate your life to this profession.

356
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,760
To deeply experience

357
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:38,320
what artifact restoration truly is.

358
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:45,480
Let's go.

359
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:46,440
First time out,

360
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:47,680
my legs are sore.

361
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,280
Me too.

362
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,680
Let's go get milk tea.

363
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:50,800
Cheer up.

364
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,930
What is this called?

365
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,120
Overcoming difficulties.

366
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:53,880
Okay.

367
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,320
I'm leaving. Bye.

368
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,400
I want half sugar.

369
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,960
Let's go to the same place, okay?

370
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,120
The same place again?

371
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,580
But I think theirs is good.

372
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:01,240
Let's go.

373
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:01,770
Let's go.

374
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:03,320
It's my treat today.

375
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:03,920
Heading home.

376
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:04,640
Thank you, young master.

377
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,040
Bye.

378
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:05,880
Bye, bye.

379
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,040
Zhao Xiaocen.

380
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:19,880
Take this.

381
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,040
Thank you.

382
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,720
What were you doing just now?

383
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,600
It was so hard to piece together,

384
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:30,760
so...

385
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,570
Do you think you can piece it all together?

386
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,040
I...

387
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,330
Let's add each other on WeChat.

388
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:43,770
Is that okay?

389
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,160
S-Sure.

390
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:17,040
Thank you for the band-aid.

391
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:23,050
You're welcome.

392
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:25,460
Good night.

393
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,119
Good night.

394
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:28,640
Xu Xiao.

395
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,480
What kind of person are you exactly?

396
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,860
What kind of profile picture is this?

397
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:38,210
Why hasn't he posted anything on his Moments?

398
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,320
Oh no.

399
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,160
Sleep.

400
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:05,080
Mr. Liang announced that

401
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,280
we'll visit the Imperial Kiln Museum on Friday.

402
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:09,610
Gather at the school gate at 8:00 AM sharp.

403
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:16,960
My name is...

404
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,530
My name is Zhao Xiaocen.

405
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:24,020
Sir, I don't know what to say anymore.

406
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:24,520
Good.

407
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,080
Cheers!

408
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:26,320
Come on, cheers!

409
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,320
Come on.

410
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:27,650
Okay.

411
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,960
Cheers.

412
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,880
Let's add each other on WeChat.

413
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:34,640
Is that okay?

414
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,840
How exactly does everyone see me?

415
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:53,280
This is it.

416
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,320
Look over there.

417
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:55,160
It's so big.

418
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:56,800
So beautiful.

419
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,040
I come here often.

420
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:58,920
So fancy.

421
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,320
Students, this is

422
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:02,640
the director of the Jingdezhen Imperial Kiln Museum,

423
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,500
Director Zhou.

424
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:04,600
Hello, Director.

425
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:05,600
Hello, students.

426
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:07,760
Welcome to the Imperial Kiln Museum.

427
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:09,920
This visit

428
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:11,480
is jointly organized by the Imperial Kiln Museum

429
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:13,600
and the Ceramic University.

430
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,640
I am glad to see so many

431
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:18,000
young people interested in

432
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,600
cultural relics and their protection.

433
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:20,720
Our museum

434
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,760
houses over a thousand pieces of rejected tribute porcelain

435
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:26,320
from the official kilns of the Yuan, Ming, and Qing dynasties,

436
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:29,480
restored by the Jingdezhen Ceramic Archaeological Institute.

437
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:31,840
Many of them are unique and unmatchable.

438
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,800
You could say that one day

439
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,800
is hardly enough to see everything.

440
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:38,880
So, I welcome you to come to our museum often

441
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,760
when you have time in the future.

442
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:41,720
Okay.

443
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,000
Now let me

444
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:45,400
show you around personally.

445
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,640
Okay.

446
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:47,240
Let's go. This way.

447
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:48,370
Sorry to bother you.

448
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:51,400
The display and design of the Imperial Kiln Museum

449
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,680
It uses a layout of connected aisle display cases

450
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:55,200
and individual ones.

451
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:56,560
Each exhibit is provided

452
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:58,960
with an explanation plaque in both Chinese and English.

453
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:01,490
You can refer to these explanation materials

454
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,820
to keep up with my pace.

455
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:04,440
Come.

456
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,500
Everyone, keep up.

457
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,200
Let's go to the exhibition hall over there.

458
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,800
Thank you for your hard work, Director Zhou.

459
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:09,730
You have no idea.

460
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:15,560
Cricket jars.

461
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,880
Can these be considered cultural relics?

462
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:20,040
These are cricket jars from the Xuande period of the Ming dynasty.

463
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,720
Emperor Xuande loved cricket fighting.

464
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,320
This student is quite right.

465
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,960
In folk legends, there is a saying of the 'Peaceful Son of Heaven'

466
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,640
and the 'Cricket Emperor',

467
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:29,050
which refers to Xuande.

468
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,080
Emperor Xuanzong passed away from illness at the age of 36.

469
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:36,010
His eldest son, Zhu Qizhen, succeeded to the throne at the age of eight.

470
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,700
Grand Empress Dowager Zhang,

471
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,560
to prevent the young emperor

472
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,920
from losing himself in playthings like his father,

473
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:44,980
ordered all the playthings in the palace to be removed.

474
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,400
Xuande's cricket jars

475
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,450
were mostly destroyed as a result.

476
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:50,640
Later,

477
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:53,720
several pieces of blue and white porcelain were discovered in Jingdezhen,

478
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:57,000
and these Xuande cricket jars were restored.

479
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,240
So even the emperor was managed by someone?

480
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:04,440
No matter what official you are, your mother manages you.

481
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,200
Okay, that's all for today's explanation.

482
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:11,120
I hope through your visit today,

483
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:13,680
you'll fall in love with the Imperial Kiln and Jingdezhen.

484
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:14,840
Thank you, Curator Zhou.

485
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,120
For the rest of the time,

486
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,000
you are free to explore.

487
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:17,840
You can go anywhere

488
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:18,840
you want to see.

489
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:19,560
Okay.

490
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:20,480
Curator Zhou, after you.

491
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,120
Okay.

492
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:26,640
Wu Jing.

493
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,200
Coming.

494
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,200
Look at this one.

495
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,040
Wow, this is so pretty.

496
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,440
It's beautiful.

497
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:34,600
Look at this.

498
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:37,840
There's a duck over there.

499
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:38,720
A duck.

500
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:40,480
Beautiful.

501
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:44,840
Like this.

502
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:46,440
Come.

503
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:49,080
Three, two, one.

504
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:50,440
Look at this.

505
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,040
Let me see.

506
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:56,040
Three-pot communicator.

507
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,520
What is this used for?

508
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,520
This is a great unsolved mystery in the ceramics world.

509
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:05,180
Most people can't answer you.

510
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:08,400
Regarding this three-pot communicator,

511
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,720
there is a lack of documentation

512
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,960
and no related artifacts for reference,

513
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:14,600
so scholars have different opinions on its usage.

514
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,060
Some say it's a medical and sanitary device,

515
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,840
while others say it's an offering vessel for a mosque,

516
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,840
but neither has any relevant basis.

517
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,530
You are also a visitor. How do you know so much?

518
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:27,250
Maybe because it's my profession.

519
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:29,720
Yuexin,

520
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,320
let's take a photo with Suisui Duck together.

521
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:32,560
Okay.

522
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:32,890
Come.

523
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,080
Come here quickly.

524
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:35,540
Coming.

525
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:38,960
Three, two, one.

526
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:42,580
What are you doing?

527
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:50,840
This wall makes sounds.

528
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:52,770
Didn't you know?

529
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:57,540
The walls of the entire Imperial Kiln Museum

530
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,170
are built with kiln bricks.

531
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,730
Gently tapping the kiln bricks

532
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:04,300
creates resonance in the gaps between them,

533
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,340
producing a melodious sound.

534
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:13,640
This entire museum

535
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,300
is like a musical instrument.

536
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:27,930
Do you hear that?

537
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:50,300
Do you have time today?

538
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,370
You're here.

539
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:09,500
I prepared something for you.

540
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:10,800
Have a seat first.

541
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:11,680
Wait a moment.

542
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,960
I saw the previous plate was broken,

543
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,490
and you weren't very happy.

544
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,280
So based on my memory

545
00:25:43,320 --> 00:25:44,920
of the plate's size and style,

546
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,050
I made a similar one.

547
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:48,970
This is just the plain body.

548
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:52,050
It will look very similar to the old one after firing.

549
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:56,200
You mean you can revive it?

550
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:58,840
Reviving it is an exaggeration.

551
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:00,100
But if you're willing,

552
00:26:00,280 --> 00:26:02,540
you can draw the original patterns on it.

553
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:04,050
You can do it anyway.

554
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:10,080
What's wrong?

555
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:11,410
Nothing.

556
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:50,060
Then the next step is glazing and firing.

557
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:54,200
Let's give it a name.

558
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:55,560
A name?

559
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:58,640
Don't the porcelain pieces in the museum

560
00:26:58,640 --> 00:26:59,720
all have names?

561
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,480
We fired this together.

562
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:04,700
I think it's very meaningful.

563
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:07,720
Then how about calling it

564
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:10,840
'Fish Playing Among Lotus Leaves'?

565
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,800
Can't we pick a shorter name?

566
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:21,440
Then let's call it Xiaoqing.

567
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,360
Xiaoqing?

568
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:26,800
Okay.
